node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Arnar Kristjansson | Iceland in Iceland with @simona_br_photography, and @withfoundation.

node.text:
"Inception" City of massive basalt rock towers rises above the fog . Probably one of the most unique situations I have been in . Witnessing the soft hazy fog streaming from below giving the perfect illusion of those rocks reaching from infinity. 

This image is now available @withfoundation

.
#iceland 
@beyondthelands  @simona_br_photography
_______________

www.beyondthelands.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Arnar Kristjansson | Iceland in Hornbjarg with @simona_br_photography. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
From a recent trip into the far west to Hornbjarg , which can be reached by boat . Spent 3 days around that area with zero connection which I loved . After constant rain the skies finally opened up with this amazing rainbow covered around the mist . If you plan to visit that area I highly recommend staying a few days , well worth it 🌧🌅

.
#iceland 
@beyondthelands  @simona_br_photography
_______________

www.beyondthelands.com

node.text:
Beautiful morning at Strútsfoss waterfall in the East,  extremely colorful fall with basalt lava and red and brown sediments. If you're lucky you might catch some reindeers while hiking over there 😎

.
#iceland 
@beyondthelands  @simona_br_photography
_______________

node.text:
🇮🇸Hæ hó jibbí jey 🇮🇸 gleðilegan þjóðhátíðardag ! 🌧 Today is our Independence day on our beautiful island in the North Atlantic . 

This image summarize the Icelandic mood and spirit for me ,  chaos and storm but in the end there is always light in the end of the tunnel "þetta reddast" 🇮🇸😎

.
#iceland 
@beyondthelands  @simona_br_photography
_______________
